<br>
Somewhere in one of the threads I've inhabited here recently, Vainne says &quot;It doesn't have to be this way,&quot; and she's right.  Fact is, relationships between the larger guilds have improved over the past year, there's just a little bit less of that wild-west feeling.  Chances of an actual race on a given day have been diminished by the vastness of the raiding content, and anyone at the level of ToS, ToN, TWC and above has an innate understanding of the unwritten rules of the game, and we generally don't put ourselves in positions where we are vulnerable to each other.<br>
<br>
Its also pretty clear that the leaders of the elemental capable guilds have at least some comittment to cooperation.  Backflagging agreements have sprung up on (almost) all sides to ease the incessant pain of having to whack Magnetic Bejesus for the 800th time so that 3 more recruits can get into the Planes.  Some guilds actually talk to each other regularly to avoid butting heads.  This is all far from sweetness and light, but its also far removed from the barefisted brawl that it could be.<br>
<br>
In the past six months, there has been a tremendous shakeout among the larger guilds on this server, produced by the pressures of raiding in PoP and the high end of Luclin.  Some guilds have disappeared, some are shadows of their former selves, some have consolidated, and a very small group have thrived and continued to advance.  The leaders of these successful guilds know intimately just how much pressure and stress is involved in advancing through the high end of the game, contesting not only with herding 70+ man raids through buggy scripted events, but with other guilds competing for access to those same events.  I think the growing raprochement between the guilds, overt or not, is evidence of a universal desire for there to be less energy going into pissing on each others petunias.  <br>
<br>
To put it a bit more simply, game is hard enough without being at each other's throats constantly.  I try to remember this, generally I succeed, but to my chagrin I occasionally forget, and all of a sudden I'm climbing the ramparts with a torch in my hand and blood in my eye.  And all because some dumb kid pulled a stunt that he now has cause to regret.<br>
<br>
I'm looking at my posts here of the past few days and the one that stands out to me is the one where I condemn TWC as a whole, saying that nothing they can possibly say will convince me of jack, because to me they are all liars.  Now, I don't like TWC, they have been the bull in our path for far too long for me to be even remotely chummy with them.  But I know in my head (the big one) that the majority of them are not hellspawn.  Some of them used to be guildmates, and are still on my list of folks I like.  And while we have had some pretty brutal races for Seru and Ssra mobs recently, with plenty of knees and elbows being thrown around, none of it reached the level of what we used to be dealing with in NToV so long ago.  Sorry if it waters down your rep guys, but TWC is annoying, and its pushy, but you do actually have some standards, you've proved it more than once recently.<br>
<br>
So I come here to say this.  TWC are not demons, they do not lie with each breath they take.  I hope that something like normal guild relations can occur between us someday.  I think that would be a good thing for both guilds. Meanwhile, we would appreciate it if you would keep your younger/more foolish members out from under our feet.  Do that, and we can be something like cordial even.  For my own part, I plan to stop throwing bombs, and to ignore the ceaseless and reflexive provocations that are par for the course here in the Blast Furnace.<br>
<br>
Who knows, we might all have more fun. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nayl7>Nayl7</A> at: 9/5/03 6:55 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anduransaryrn>Anduran Saryrn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/images/avatars/187040ee3deea6510867d.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Doing it Dingo Style!</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(9/5/03 7:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3526.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Morning after</span><hr size=1> I hear ya, fighting on the blast furnace achieves nothing.  The game was designed poorly, one family eats and due to that another family staves, lack of content drives everyone at the same level against each other.  It sucks, hopefully LDoN will fix this somewhat. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=339789"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vicour1/AnduranSig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anduransaryrn>Anduran Saryrn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/images/avatars/187040ee3deea6510867d.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Doing it Dingo Style!</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(9/5/03 8:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3526.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top a