We are a guild alliance - full alliance as in every raid is with the 3 membership guilds involved - even the night shift - we are bored what mobs are up raids like AL, AoW etc. We also tend to group together and such. <br>
<br>
Perhaps the only reason we are not a single guild is due to history and guild culture - DW is a more international guild, and the languages in guildchat tends to be Japanese and English with some others thrown in for good measure (you see Dutch and German from time to time). Forces and UB are both Japanese guilds, and have been in the game for years - they are more of a close knit group of friends with a few recruits added from time to time.<br>
<br>
The alliance works as to get to potime we need to be allied, but we keep our own identities as guilds - we kinda get the best of both worlds. Every guild member is as dedicated to making the alliance work as their own guild working - and I would say for about 85% of the time SR could be my guild as much as DW.<br>
<br>
I must admit when the alliance was first started I didnt expect it to work - but it does and it works well - if you can accept working 110% with another guild(s) and accepting orders / directions from raidleaders outside your guild I would recommend being part of an alliance to anybody.<br>
<br>
